-\subsection{The Koide formula and SU(3)\texorpdfstring{$_{\mathrm{gen}}$}{gen}}
-\label{sec:koide}
-
-In 1981, Yoshio Koide discovered that the three charged lepton masses satisfy:
-\begin{equation}
-K \equiv \frac{m_e+m_\mu+m_\tau}{(\sqrt{m_e}+\sqrt{m_\mu}+\sqrt{m_\tau})^2} = \frac{2}{3}.
-\end{equation}
-Using 2022 PDG values, $K=0.666661$, agreeing with $2/3$ to one part in $10^5$. The Standard Model does not derive this relation; in RA, it is a theorem of BDG integer arithmetic, formally verified in Lean~4 (\texttt{koide\_formula} in \texttt{RA\_Koide.lean}, zero \texttt{sorry}).
