-\subsection{The $N_{\mathrm{eff}}=L_q^3$ identification}
-
-The identification $N_{\mathrm{eff}}=L_q^3=64$ is introduced as a working hypothesis. It produces a universal relation $\mu_p=\alpha_{\mathrm{EM}}/32$ that is independent of the confinement length, and gives the observed proton mass to $0.3\%$. The identification is conjectural (CN in the sense of \S1): its motivation is structural---the proton's confinement region should contain $L_q^3$ independent actualization sites in depth-space, corresponding to the 3D volume of the confinement lattice---but this is a physical picture rather than a derivation from the growth rule.
