-\end{equation}
-The observed proton mass is $938.3$\,MeV; the match is $0.3\%$. The exponent $28=5\times 5+3$ decomposes as five powers of $32=2^5$ from equation (26) plus $c_4=2^3$ from equation (22). The inputs are $m_P$ (the single dimensionful scale in RA), $\alpha_{\mathrm{EM}}=1/137.036$ (derived in \S3.2), and the conjectural identification $N_{\mathrm{eff}}=L_q^3$.
